---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Brett Zink">
  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title">About Me</h2>
    <p style="color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      I spent my early career inside a Fortune 500 bank's security organization: running
      penetration tests against corporate networks and facilities, building out enterprise
      SIEM infrastructure, leading vendor evaluations for network access control,
      and helping shape how a large financial institution approached security
      operations. That experience gave me a permanent bias toward understanding
      how systems fail before deciding how to build them.
    </p>
    <p style="color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      From there I co-founded a SaaS startup on .NET and Azure, then spent
      nearly a decade as a software engineer building backend services and
      system integrations across healthcare, government, and justice software.
      Along the way I became the person who also owned the CI/CD pipelines,
      the AWS infrastructure, the deployment architecture, and the security
      posture. The line between development and operations never really existed
      for me.
    </p>
    <p style="color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      Today I lead cyber security and infrastructure at Matrix Pointe Software.
      I've spent my whole career where security, infrastructure, and software
      overlap. I've never had the luxury of thinking about one without the
      others.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
